list_variables.description: CNAMEs (alternate domain names), if any, for the distribution.
list_variables.name: Aliases

list_variables.description: A list of CacheBehavior types for the distribution.
list_variables.name: CacheBehaviors

list_variables.description: Whether CloudFront replaces HTTP status codes in the 4xx and                      5xx range with custom error messages before returning the response                   to the viewer.
list_variables.name: CustomErrorResponses

list_variables.description: A list of origins for this CloudFront distribution. For each origin, you can specify                   whether it is an Amazon S3 or custom origin.
list_variables.name: Origins

variables.description: Any comments that you want to include about the distribution.
variables.name: Comment

variables.description: The default cache behavior that is triggered if you do not specify the                      CacheBehavior property or if files don't match any of the values                   of PathPattern in the CacheBehavior property.
variables.name: DefaultCacheBehavior

variables.description: The object (such as index.html) that you want CloudFront to request from                   your origin when the root URL for your distribution (such as                      http://example.com/) is requested.
variables.name: DefaultRootObject

variables.description: Controls whether the distribution is enabled to accept end user requests for content.
variables.name: Enabled

variables.description: Controls whether access logs are written for the distribution. To turn on                   access logs, specify this property.
variables.name: Logging

variables.description: The price class that corresponds with the maximum price that you want to pay                   for the CloudFront service. For more information, see Choosing the Price Class in the                      Amazon CloudFront Developer Guide.
variables.name: PriceClass

variables.description: Specifies restrictions on who or how viewers can access your content.
variables.name: Restrictions

variables.description: The certificate to use when viewers use HTTPS to request objects.
variables.name: ViewerCertificate
